Body: Description: When the client tries to uninstall the agent in one of the devices he has, at first, he gets an error of a missing dll package wich is "MSIInstallerDLL.dll" file. When the client replaces the dll file with another dll file from another device with the same agent, it all works but the agent wizard appears to him asking for a password they don't have configured on the server.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Emil Podar, Iván Jiménez
What We've Learned Updated: The customer could not uninstall the EPP Client from one of the machines

Next Steps Updated: During a remote session we used the ZAP tool in order to remove the EPP Client.
Waiting for the customer to confirm if the ticket can be closed.
